      "title": "Southside School District",
      "text": "A short bike ride to highly regarded Southside Elementary — and available in August, so you're settled before the school year starts. Ten minutes to both Siesta Key and Downtown Sarasota."
    },
    {
      "title": "Elevated Peace of Mind",
      "text": "Built in 2013 and elevated 22 feet above sea level in an X flood zone — modern construction and genuine coastal peace of mind, without flood-zone premiums."
    },
    {
      "title": "Saltwater Pool & Tropical Lanai",
      "text": "Southern exposure fills the coastal-casual great room and updated kitchen with light, overlooking the private saltwater pool beneath flowering plumeria. Pocketing sliders make indoor-outdoor living seamless."
    },
    {
      "title": "A Layout That Works",
      "text": "All four bedrooms up — a 13'×15' master suite plus three flexible bedrooms (one with Murphy bed) — with the 16'×17' great room and kitchen on the main floor and a 12'×12' bonus room for media, play, or lounge."
    },
    {
      "title": "Turn-Key, Truly",
      "text": "Pool care, lawn care and internet included in the rent. Artificial turf, mature landscaping, and multiple outdoor gathering areas keep maintenance near zero. Furnished or unfurnished — your choice."
    },
    {
      "title": "Southside Village Living",
      "text": "The historic Granada neighborhood, steps from Southside Village dining. The 20'×20' two-car garage includes a Tesla Level 2 EV charger and room for bikes and beach gear. Pets considered case-by-case with owner approval and deposit."
